Here we go...I started this journey at 229 pounds and weighed in at 185 lbs. this morning, I say Yah!! to this cause sometimes we forget the journey of what it took to get this far but I still have more....the frustrating part is I was so close to the 50 pound loss when our @ww workshops closed up and I really struggled with missing my coach Karen and the accountability the weekly meetings brought me.  From the onset of COVID it was one thing after another with the first two weeks before the outbreak my mom broke both legs and ended up in a rehabilitation center and was there for three weeks, then lived with me for 7 weeks, well by then I was just maintaining within a few pounds and am happy that I’m still only up around 3 to 4 pounds.  Well I’m treating this like a #freshstart for several reasons... holidays are fast approaching, I’m feeling goal oriented again, cooler temps will get me out walking more or earlier, new foods!  Hoping to get to 50 pounds or close to it and definitely by Thanksgiving.  Well today I have a tea to go to with my girls and their boyfriends so I’ll order a salad and have a treat. If you want to join just screen shot my last post or it’s in my highlights under WW. Just use the hashtag #leanforhalloween so I can find you and support you along the way.  Good luck!!👍🏻 🎃
